AGI - A Manhattan jury found Donald Trump guilty of forging corporate documents in relation to Stormy Daniels' story. The Manhattan Tribunal declared the tycoon guilty of all 34 counts of charges > on the case, or having tampered with tax and financial documents to hide the payment put into place to buy the silence of the pornstar who, in 2016, in the full presidential campaign, threatened to reveal that he had sex with him years before.&nbsp;It is the first president in the history of the United States to run convicted for a crime, but this will not prevent him from being. The judge will pronounce the sentence on 11 July. >
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
The twelve jurors had to find unanimity for each of the thirty-four heads of crime. Trump looked straight ahead while the verdict was read in the Court. The former President did not initially move. Then he grabbed his son Eric's hand, and he held it quickly before he left. Shortly after the first words to the press: "It's a 'shark' a 'made process'." For the magnate "the real verdict will be expressed by the people on November 5. Everyone knows what happened here." His lawyer, Todd Blanche, assured that he will file an appeal against the verdict of guilt as soon as possible. Speaking with Cnn, the lawyer reported that the former president will carry out the post-process motions and "if this is not successful, as soon as we can appeal, we will do it". According to Blanche, constitutional rights of his client have been violated "in many ways". Responding to Jesse Watters' questions about FoxNews, the lawyer claimed that the former president "had no fair trial."
